WEBVTT

00:00.736 --> 00:02.750
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

00:05.682 --> 00:07.332
<i>There are few words</i>
<i>that bring more joy</i>

00:07.433 --> 00:11.029
<i>to value-seeking Midwesterners</i>
<i>than "All U Can Eat."</i>

00:11.165 --> 00:12.290
Don't eat that!

00:12.418 --> 00:13.920
We're going
to King Henry's Buffet.

00:14.013 --> 00:15.132
Oh, are you crazy?

00:15.243 --> 00:17.995
Do you not understand?
We got a squatters coupon!

00:18.085 --> 00:20.751
We get to pick a table
and stay there <i>all</i> day.

00:20.836 --> 00:22.505
We're having lunch,
supper, dinner,

00:22.591 --> 00:24.408
second dinner, and dessert.

00:24.495 --> 00:25.825
Okay.
I got my game plan.

00:26.009 --> 00:28.945
I'm going cold to hot,
concentrating on meats.

00:29.103 --> 00:31.189
You want to beat the house,
you got to load up on the meats.

00:31.328 --> 00:33.405
Now, remember,
when we get to King Henry's,

00:33.510 --> 00:35.980
everyone has to have
<i>one</i> green on their plate.

00:36.662 --> 00:37.816
I'm kidding!

00:37.893 --> 00:39.759
How weird would that be
if I was serious?

00:39.837 --> 00:42.108
I'm going all soups.
I love their soups.

00:42.200 --> 00:44.558
Thousand Island, ranch,
blue cheese--

00:44.668 --> 00:46.693
Brick, those are
salad dressings.

00:46.823 --> 00:48.079
No, I don't think so.

00:48.146 --> 00:49.807
They have ladles and bowls
right next to them.

00:50.036 --> 00:52.800
I'm home!

00:52.981 --> 00:56.130
Okay. I'm here. I'm starving.
Let's go.

00:56.225 --> 00:57.163
Right after church.

00:57.238 --> 00:58.519
Oh, whoa! Church?

00:58.623 --> 00:59.822
We have to go to church first.

00:59.905 --> 01:02.455
We should at least thank God
for our squatters coupon.

01:02.542 --> 01:04.150
Oh, come on!
I don't want to sit in church.

01:04.233 --> 01:06.182
I can't take Reverend Hayver
on an empty stomach.

01:06.289 --> 01:07.582
No, no, no,
we have a guest minister--

01:07.724 --> 01:10.793
Reverend Eric Deveaux
from <i>Cleveland.</i>

01:10.910 --> 01:12.171
Very charismatic.

01:12.275 --> 01:14.762
He and Reverend Hayver are
on a minister-exchange program.

01:14.847 --> 01:17.459
Even dad likes him.
He's very entertaining.

01:17.569 --> 01:18.544
I'm gonna tell you something
right now.

01:18.661 --> 01:20.360
You can't outrun the Lord!

01:20.563 --> 01:21.919
Where you gonna run to, son?

01:22.030 --> 01:27.279
♪ Our voices will ring
foreve-e-e-r ♪

01:27.382 --> 01:33.075
♪ as o-o-o-o-o-o-o-one ♪

01:33.699 --> 01:35.630
Blows Reverend Hayver
out of the water.

01:36.920 --> 01:39.070
Ooh. Baby sister's
looking at colleges.

01:39.159 --> 01:39.796
Let's see.

01:39.900 --> 01:42.017
Purdue-- Pur-don't.

01:42.133 --> 01:44.571
IU-- <i>I</i> don't see <i>you</i>
<i>getting in there.</i>

01:45.781 --> 01:46.715
Wait. No.

01:47.043 --> 01:49.012
No, no, no!
Don't even think about it!

01:49.089 --> 01:50.683
East Indiana State
is <i>my</i> school!

01:50.826 --> 01:52.438
Mom, dad, make her stop!
Seriously!

01:52.561 --> 01:54.744
You know, I-I can go
wherever I want, Axl.

01:54.874 --> 01:56.455
You can't stop me
from thinking about it.

01:56.576 --> 01:58.703
I'm thinking about it right now!

01:58.818 --> 01:59.766
What?

01:59.853 --> 02:01.888
In fact, I'm gonna be
thinking about it all day!

02:01.952 --> 02:03.313
No. Make her stop
thinking about it. Make her--

02:03.403 --> 02:07.125
- ♪ Oh, East Indiana, we will fight
for you ♪ - No! That's not--

02:07.225 --> 02:08.889
- ♪ East Indiana, we will always
be true ♪ - Don't sing our fight song!

02:09.006 --> 02:10.988
Do you see this? Do you see
what's happening here?

02:11.160 --> 02:13.748
- No. Come on. - ♪ We shall defeat
them with our tongues! ♪

02:13.831 --> 02:14.736
No!

02:17.964 --> 02:19.835
Axl, your sister can go
wherever she wants.

02:19.934 --> 02:21.277
Sue, stop tormenting
your brother.

02:21.378 --> 02:22.955
Now, come on--
we got to go worship the Lord

02:23.048 --> 02:24.382
and then gorge ourselves.

02:27.003 --> 02:28.414
Who didn't want
to come here this morning?

02:28.491 --> 02:30.193
Show of hands.
Come on. Be honest.

02:30.279 --> 02:32.262
You're tired, it's early.

02:32.426 --> 02:33.670
You stayed up too late

02:33.750 --> 02:36.492
watching back-to-back episodes
of Burn Notice.

02:37.322 --> 02:39.759
- Put your hands down! - Okay, I see.
You're being accountable there.

02:39.858 --> 02:41.772
That's what I want to talk
to y'all about this morning--

02:42.508 --> 02:43.639
accountability.

02:43.717 --> 02:45.480
There's no way you're
getting into East Indiana State.

02:45.580 --> 02:47.060
I can do whatever I want, Axl.

02:47.186 --> 02:48.840
In fact, I am gonna pray to God

02:48.938 --> 02:50.885
that I get into
East Indiana State.

02:50.974 --> 02:52.074
What?
Don't you dare do that.

02:52.165 --> 02:52.923
Dear God--

02:53.026 --> 02:54.221
- Stop doing that.
- You can't control me!

02:54.363 --> 02:55.703
Fine--
I'm gonna double-pray

02:55.774 --> 02:56.738
that you <i>don't</i> go
to East Indiana.

02:56.885 --> 02:58.012
- Don't you dare!
- God, please--

02:59.536 --> 03:01.662
When you see
a stranger on the street and...

03:01.787 --> 03:03.630
- God, please don't let her go
to East Indiana State. - Stop it, Axl!

03:03.727 --> 03:04.359
Ow!

03:05.713 --> 03:06.540
Mike.

03:06.742 --> 03:08.555
Oh, you have
freakishly strong fingers.

03:08.759 --> 03:11.073
Hey! Knock it off.

03:11.154 --> 03:12.419
I'm serious.

03:12.572 --> 03:14.580
- God, please don't--
- Ow! Don't you--

03:14.657 --> 03:17.003
Axl, Sue! Stop it!
Stop it right now!

03:19.027 --> 03:20.933
I c--

03:25.554 --> 03:27.889
At any rate,
the Lord loves you.

03:27.983 --> 03:30.028
He loves your friends
that didn't make it, either.

03:32.044 --> 03:32.949
Hi.

03:34.602 --> 03:36.279
You're the Hecks, right?

03:36.509 --> 03:38.967
Could I see you for a moment?

03:41.331 --> 03:44.885
Let me just say
we are so sorry about earlier.

03:44.985 --> 03:46.821
This will <i>never</i> happen again.

03:47.002 --> 03:48.553
I-I never
talked to my family

03:48.650 --> 03:50.848
about not throwing
sacred books in church,

03:50.976 --> 03:54.148
but, in my defense,
I didn't think I had to.

03:54.290 --> 03:56.596
Folks, I don't want to take up
too much of your time,

03:56.799 --> 04:00.259
but it seems like you're under
a great deal of stress.

04:00.382 --> 04:02.889
No. We're fine.
Just a regular amount of stress.

04:03.006 --> 04:03.879
Yeah.

04:03.977 --> 04:06.664
Look. We kind of have...
somewhere we have to be.

04:06.780 --> 04:07.950
But we're fine.
We are.

04:08.037 --> 04:09.483
That was just
an isolated incident.

04:09.709 --> 04:11.903
Well, you know,
it's not just this one day.

04:12.035 --> 04:14.886
Uh, Reverend Hayver said,
you know,

04:14.988 --> 04:18.759
that there's been some issues,
a-a little history.

04:18.841 --> 04:19.668
Am-- am I right?

04:19.745 --> 04:21.298
- History? What history?
- The van.

04:21.403 --> 04:22.633
We gave it right back.

04:22.728 --> 04:24.732
Now, I assure you--
nobody's on trial here.

04:24.821 --> 04:27.840
I just like to reach out
to families in crisis

04:27.985 --> 04:29.620
and, you know,
offer some counsel.

04:29.717 --> 04:31.977
As the former
assistant spiritual advisor

04:32.088 --> 04:34.321
for the Cleveland Browns
for 1 and 3/4 of a season,

04:34.494 --> 04:38.022
consider me here
to lift you up.

04:38.198 --> 04:42.180
But to do that,
I got to able to get underneath.

04:42.307 --> 04:43.172
You know what I'm saying?

04:43.291 --> 04:48.351
And the deeper I dig,
the higher <i>we</i> can go.

04:48.439 --> 04:51.593
Oh, we're plenty high.
We are up there in the clouds.

04:52.357 --> 04:55.416
I mean, we fight, sure,
but we have fun, right?

04:55.595 --> 04:57.667
We do all kinds
of fun stuff together.

04:57.759 --> 04:59.143
We, um...

04:59.515 --> 05:01.984
eat... and...

05:02.112 --> 05:02.914
Come on, people.

05:03.017 --> 05:05.311
Tell him all the other
fun family stuff we do.

05:06.468 --> 05:08.440
Oh!
We play Twizzlestick.

05:08.583 --> 05:10.584
It's a really fun game
I invented.

05:10.718 --> 05:11.859
It's where you're in a room

05:11.949 --> 05:13.259
and you have
one body part showing

05:13.366 --> 05:15.327
and if nobody notices you
when they come in,

05:15.437 --> 05:16.665
you get a point.

05:22.645 --> 05:23.781
Twizzlestick!

05:26.200 --> 05:27.355
Twizzlestick!

05:28.234 --> 05:29.258
Twizzlestick!

05:31.643 --> 05:34.355
So, you all really get into
this, uh, Twizzlestick, huh?

05:34.448 --> 05:36.296
- Oh... sure. - So much fun.
- Not really.

05:36.392 --> 05:37.786
Love playing Dorklestick.

05:38.232 --> 05:40.961
You know what? This has
been great-- really helpful.

05:41.068 --> 05:42.470
But we're good.
We are.

05:42.554 --> 05:43.980
It's my fault.
I threw the book.

05:44.077 --> 05:45.379
But we're--
we're really good.

05:45.456 --> 05:46.205
Aren't we all good?

05:46.291 --> 05:47.908
- So good.
- We love each other so much!

05:48.029 --> 05:49.048
You sure?

05:49.149 --> 05:51.391
'Cause, you know,
when that teakettle's whistling,

05:51.567 --> 05:53.829
it's time
to take it off the stove.

05:53.923 --> 05:55.915
Yeah, but our teakettle
is fine.

05:56.000 --> 05:57.555
In fact, we're all heading out

05:57.679 --> 06:00.033
to eat together as a family
right now.

06:00.222 --> 06:02.669
Okay.
Well, fair enough.

06:02.901 --> 06:07.408
But if there's ever <i>anything</i>
<i>you'd like to talk about,</i>

06:07.506 --> 06:09.072
my door is always open.

06:09.175 --> 06:11.190
Nope. This was great.
Thank you.

06:11.258 --> 06:12.040
All right, then.

06:12.137 --> 06:13.877
You guys have yourselves
a blessed Sunday.

06:14.008 --> 06:15.813
That's exactly
what we're gonna do.

06:16.344 --> 06:18.063
Sometimes I feel invisible.

06:20.000 --> 06:26.074
Advertise your product or brand here
